			title: "Framed Blocks"
			icon: "framedblocks:framed_cube"
			description: [
				"§6Framed Blocks§f takes a different approach to decoration than CopyCats."
				"§fInstead of shape-first, it is §efunction-first:§f a full-size block"
				"§fthat looks like any other block — but is hollow and has a full hitbox."
				""
				"§eFramed Cube:§r"
				"§7• §eCrafting:§7 §e6 Sticks§7 in an outline (like chest but sticks only)."
				"§7• §eRight-click with any block§7 to apply that block's texture."
				"§7• The Framed Cube keeps the applied texture permanently."
				""
				"§eWhy use Framed Blocks over CopyCats:§r"
				"§7• §eFramed Cube§7 is a §efull block§7 — full light blocking, full hitbox."
				"§7  CopyCat Panel is 1/16 thick — no collision mass."
				"§7• §eFramed Slope§7 — a sloped full-block wedge, great for rooflines."
				"§7• §eFramed Slope Panel§7 — thinner slope for eaves and overhangs."
				"§7• §eFramed Stairs§7 — stair shape with any block texture."
				""
				"§eCombining CopyCats and Framed Blocks:§r"
				"§7• §eFramed Cube§7 for exterior walls and corners (full blocks)."
				"§7• §eCopyCat Panel§7 for accent strips, machinery cladding, and windows."
				"§7• §eDecorativeBlocks Beams§7 overhead with CopyCat Panels between them"
				"§7  = a perfect ceiling that matches any wall material."
				""
				"§a► Craft and hold a Framed Cube."
			]
			dependencies: ["000E0002" "000E0003" "000E0004"]
